{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"77e449b7-d393-4e10-9b83-ffbd46f07cfb","content":"## Most likely cause: JDK version mismatch\n\n**.NET 9+ MAUI Android requires JDK 21**, but you have JDK 17. JDK 17 is only sufficient for .NET 8 MAUI.\n\n### Fix\n\nInstall the Microsoft OpenJDK 21 (recommended for MAUI) or Adoptium Temurin 21:\n\n```bash\n# Option A: Microsoft OpenJDK (recommended)\nbrew install --cask microsoft-openjdk@21\n\n# Option B: Adoptium Temurin 21\nbrew install --cask temurin@21\n```\n\nThen update `JAVA_HOME`:\n\n```bash\n# For Microsoft OpenJDK 21:\nexport JAVA_HOME=\"/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/microsoft-21.jdk/Contents/Home\"\n\n# For Temurin 21:\nexport JAVA_HOME=\"/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-21.jdk/Contents/Home\"\n```\n\nAdd the export to your `~/.zshrc` (or `~/.bash_profile`) to persist it.\n\n### Verify\n\n```bash\njava -version   # Should show 21.x\ndotnet build -t:ValidateJavaVersion\n```\n\n> **Tip:** If you're on **.NET 8**, JDK 17 *is* correct — check the actual error message for a different root cause (e.g., `JAVA_HOME` pointing to a JRE instead of JDK, or an Android SDK tools issue). Let me know the exact error if you'd like more targeted help.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"92c1c9a2-e33c-4810-9d22-d5f902ca5298","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is having a .NET MAUI Android build failure related to Java. They have Adoptium Temurin JDK 17.0.12 installed. Let me think about what common issues exist with .NET MAUI Android builds and Java.\n\nThe most common issue here is that .NET MAUI / Xamarin Android builds require a specific JDK version. Starting with .NET 8, MAUI Android requires JDK 17, which they have. But there could be a few issues:\n\n1. **JDK 21 required for newer .NET versions**: Starting with .NET 9, MAUI Android requires JDK 21. \n\nIf they're using .NET 9 or later, their JDK 17 installation won't be compatible. There's also the possibility of a JAVA_HOME path issue on macOS, where the Adoptium JDK might not be correctly configured—the path should typically point to `/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-17.jdk/Contents/Home`. Another consideration is that while .NET MAUI ships with Microsoft OpenJDK and other distributions can work, there are sometimes compatibility issues between different JDK vendors.\n\nThe most likely culprit though is a version mismatch: .NET 8 works with JDK 17, but .NET 9 requires JDK 21 instead. Since the user didn't specify their .NET version, this could easily be the problem if they've recently upgraded.","outputTokens":1039},"id":"e029a4ec-b0f7-4f21-a2c1-20b787f44e0f","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:48:59.226Z","parentId":"3cafbbcc-d2d4-4702-ba15-3131844b1f55"}
